'''Ireneusz JeleÅ''' ({{IPA-pol|irÉËnÉuÊ ËjÉlÉÉ²|-|Pl-Ireneusz_JeleÅ.ogg}}; born 9 April 1981 in [[Cieszyn]]) is a Polish [[football (soccer)|footballer]] who plays as a right-winger or [[striker]] for [[Ligue 1]] side [[Lille OSC|Lille]] and the [[Poland national football team|Polish national football team]].
==Club career== From 2002 to 2006 he played for [[WisÅa PÅock]] in the [[Ekstraklasa]]. In four seasons he scored 45 goals in 100 appearances in the Polish top league.
On 28 June 2006, JeleÅ signed for Auxerre in [[Ligue 1]]. On 9 September 2006, JeleÅ scored his first league goal for Auxerre against [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]]. On 20 October 2007, he grabbed his first hat-trick, after coming off the bench in the 71st minute against [[FC Lorient]]. In his first couple of seasons at Auxerre, JeleÅ was plagued with recurring back problems. In October 2008 he suffered a broken collarbone. He returned to action in late January 2009.<ref name="stoptherot">{{cite news | author = Piotr KoÅºmiÅski | url = http://www.uefa.com/footballeurope/news/kind=2/newsid=795199.html | title = JeleÅ out to stop the rot at Auxerre | date = 27 January 2009 | work = [[UEFA]].com | accessdate = 14 February 2009}}</ref> Auxerre's manager [[Jean Fernandez]] has described JeleÅ as the player in his squad having the most ability in front of goal.<ref name="vraiplus">{{cite news | author = Alexis Billebault | url = http://www.lequipe.fr/Football/breves2009/20090313_093904_jelen-le-vrai-plus-de-l-aja.html | title = Jelen, le vrai plus de l'AJA | date = 13 March 2009 | work = [[L'Ãquipe]] | accessdate = 21 March 2009 | language = French}}</ref> Prior to his return, Auxerre was in 17th place, barely above the relegation zone.<ref name="bonneetoile">{{cite news | author = Alexis Toledano | url = http://www.footmercato.net/zoom-sur-ireneusz-jelen-la-bonne_article34583.html | title = Zoom sur Ireneusz Jelen, la bonne Ã©toile de lâAJA | date = 23 May 2009 | work = FootMercato | accessdate = 23 May 2009 | language = French}}</ref> Upon his return, JeleÅ scored 11 goals in 16 league matches, with Auxerre advancing to 8th in the table. Despite missing part of the season, Jelen tied for 4th in the Ligue 1 goalscoring charts. In May 2009, he was voted Auxerre's Player of the Season, garnering 79% of the votes.<ref name="jadls">{{cite news | author = | url = http://www.aja.fr/siteofficiel/article.asp?NUM=3486 | title = Ireneusz Jelen, Ã©lu joueur auxerrois de la saiso